message.content:
To calculate Return on Assets (ROA), the formula is:

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}} \times 100\%
\]

Where:
- Net Profit = -1,352,379.63 (from income statement)
- Average Total Assets = \(\frac{\text{Beginning Assets} + \text{Ending Assets}}{2}\)

From balance sheet:
- Beginning Total Assets = 13,000,000.00
- Ending Total Assets = 12,385,382.42

Calculate Average Total Assets:
\[
\frac{13,000,000 + 12,385,382.42}{2} = \frac{25,385,382.42}{2} = 12,692,691.21
\]

Calculate ROA:
\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{-1,352,379.63}{12,692,691.21} \times 100\% = -0.10652 \times 100\% = -10.65\%
\]

Rounded to two decimal places, ROA = -10.65%
